"title": "8450: martyrdom",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8450",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The term “martyr” comes from the Greek word for “witness”, reminding believers that the supreme act of witness for the gospel is to give up one's life for its sake.</p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ as martyr</h2>\n<h3>Jesus Christ had to suffer and die</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark8:31\">MRK 8:31</a></strong> <em>In that Jesus Christ gives up his life, he may be thought of as a martyr. But the NT stresses that he is far more than this. Through his death alone come all the benefits of salvation, in which all believers can share.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa53:10\">ISA 53:10</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ's life is given as a ransom for believers</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt20:28\">MAT 20:28</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:45\">MRK 10:45</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:22\">LUK 9:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:11\">JHN 10:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:23\">ACT 2:23</a></p>\n<h2>Other examples of martyrdom</h2>\n<h3>Abel</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen4:8\">GEN 4:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt23:35\">MAT 23:35</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:51\">LUK 11:51</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:4\">HEB 11:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb12:24\">HEB 12:24</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John3:12\">1JN 3:12</a></p>\n<h3>Zechariah</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr24:20-2Chr24:21\">2CH 24:20–24:21</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:51\">LUK 11:51</a></p>\n<h3>John the Baptist</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt14:10-Matt14:12\">MAT 14:10–14:12</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:27-Mark6:29\">MRK 6:27–6:29</a></p>\n<h3>Stephen</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:58\">ACT 7:58</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts22:20\">ACT 22:20</a> <em>Stephen is the first martyr of the Christian church.</em></p>\n<h3>James</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts12:2\">ACT 12:2</a></p>\n<h3>Peter</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John21:18-John21:19\">JHN 21:18–21:19</a></p>\n<h3>Antipas</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:13\">REV 2:13</a></p>\n<h3>Unnamed martyrs</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs19:10\">1KI 19:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom11:3\">ROM 11:3</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh9:26\">NEH 9:26</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt23:30-Matt23:34\">MAT 23:30–23:34</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:47-Luke11:49\">LUK 11:47–11:49</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:52\">ACT 7:52</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:35-Rom8:36\">ROM 8:35–8:36</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:35\">HEB 11:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:37\">HEB 11:37</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas5:6\">JAS 5:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev11:7\">REV 11:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev13:15\">REV 13:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev16:6\">REV 16:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev17:6\">REV 17:6</a></p>\n<h2>Noble qualities of martyrs</h2>\n<h3>Courage</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan3:16-Dan3:18\">DAN 3:16–3:18</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Prayerfulness</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:59-Acts7:60\">ACT 7:59–7:60</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Self-denial</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev12:11\">REV 12:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:24\">MAT 16:24</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark8:34\">MRK 8:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:24\">LUK 9:24</a></p>\n<h3>Serenity</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:55-Acts7:56\">ACT 7:55–7:56</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Steadfastness</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:10\">REV 2:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:35\">HEB 11:35</a><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts21:13\">ACT 21:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan3:16-Dan3:18\">DAN 3:16–3:18</a></p>\n<h2>Martyrdom must be recognised as a possibility for all believers</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke21:16\">LUK 21:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:21\">MAT 10:21</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark13:12\">MRK 13:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:9\">MAT 24:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John16:2\">JHN 16:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John21:18-John21:19\">JHN 21:18–21:19</a></p>\n<h2>Reasons for martyrdom</h2>\n<h3>Refusal to engage in false worship</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan3:6\">DAN 3:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan3:16-Dan3:18\">DAN 3:16–3:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan6:7\">DAN 6:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan11:30-Dan11:33\">DAN 11:30–11:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev13:15\">REV 13:15</a></p>\n<h3>Courageous confrontation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh9:26\">NEH 9:26</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt14:2-Matt14:12\">MAT 14:2–14:12</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:17-Mark6:29\">MRK 6:17–6:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:51-Acts7:58\">ACT 7:51–7:58</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev11:7-Rev11:10\">REV 11:7–11:10</a></p>\n<h3>Public confession of Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:9\">MAT 24:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark13:12-Mark13:13\">MRK 13:12–13:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke21:16-Luke21:17\">LUK 21:16–21:17</a></p>\n<h3>A holy life</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John3:12\">1JN 3:12</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Methods of martyrdom</h2>\n<h3>Beheading</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt14:10\">MAT 14:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:16\">MRK 6:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:9\">LUK 9:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev20:4\">REV 20:4</a></p>\n<h3>Burning</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan3:11\">DAN 3:11</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor13:3\">1CO 13:3</a></p>\n<h3>Mutilation</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:37\">HEB 11:37</a></p>\n<h3>Stoning</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:58\">ACT 7:58</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:37\">HEB 11:37</a></p>\n<h3>The sword</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts12:2\">ACT 12:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:37\">HEB 11:37</a></p>\n<h3>Torture</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:35\">HEB 11:35</a></p>\n<h2>Retribution for instigators of martyrdom</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev6:9-Rev6:10\">REV 6:9–6:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt23:35\">MAT 23:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts12:1-Acts12:2\">ACT 12:1–12:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts12:23\">ACT 12:23</a></p>\n<h2>Rewards of martyrdom</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:10\">REV 2:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:39\">MAT 10:39</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev20:4\">REV 20:4</a></p>",
